I found this place just because it's near the train. The food is the best Dominican food I've ever had (and I've eaten Dominican food everywhere from Staten Island, Patterson, West Bronx, Corona, Newark and Woodhaven). The burgers, fish, steak, chicken, vegetables, any bean dish... it's all amazing and delicious.  This isn't McDonald's or 7-11, so I don't expect the food to be there in minutes. Believe me, it's worth waiting 10 minutes for! It's very good service, especially if you go in. There is no delay and it's very clean, comfortable and fast, efficient, friendly staff.
